<div class="container py-4">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-10 offset-lg-1">
      <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
          <h1 class="h3 mb-0 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">What is My Landlord Ratings?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              My Landlord Ratings is a platform that allows tenants to rate and review landlords based on their rental experiences.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">How do I use My Landlord Ratings?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              You can search for a landlord or rental property and leave a rating and review based on your experience. If a landlord record is not available, you can sign up or sign in and create one.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">Can anyone leave a review on My Landlord Ratings?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Yes. Anyone who has rented from a landlord can leave a review. Reviewers are asked to provide basic information to help support review integrity.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">Can landlords remove negative reviews?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              No. Landlords cannot remove negative reviews. However, they can respond to reviews and address issues raised by tenants.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">How can I trust the reviews?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              My Landlord Ratings encourages honest and accurate reviews to help renters make informed decisions. The platform is designed to support transparency between renters and landlords.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">Can landlords respond to reviews?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Yes. Landlords can respond to reviews to provide their perspective and address concerns raised by tenants.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">Is My Landlord Ratings free to use?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Yes. My Landlord Ratings is free to use.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="h5">Can I use My Landlord Ratings to find a new rental property?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              No. My Landlord Ratings is not a rental listing platform. However, renters can use it to research potential landlords before signing a lease agreement.
            </p>
          </div>

          <hr>

          <div class="text-center">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Need Help or Want to Offer Feedback?</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Email us at
              <a href="mailto:mylandlordratings@gmail.com">mylandlordratings@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
